==English==

===Noun===
'''quadruple double'''
#{{basketball}} The achievement of a two-digit number of any four of points scored, assists, rebounds, blocks, or steals in a single game.
#: ''The last quadruple double in the NBA was achieved by David Robinson of the San Antonio Spurs on February 17, 1994, with a monstrous 34 points, 10 rebounds, 10 assists and 10 blocks.''

